KUBERNETES + MINIKUBE PRACTICAL EXAM – COMPLETE COMMANDS & EXPECTED
 OUTPUTS
 1) START MINIKUBE
 Command:
 minikube start
 Expected Output:- Host: Running- Kubelet: Running- Kubeconfig: Configured
 2) CHECK NODE
 Command:
 kubectl get nodes
 Expected Output:- NAME = minikube- STATUS = Ready
 3) CREATE DEPLOYMENT (NGINX)
 Command:
 kubectl create deployment myngnix --image=nginx
 Expected Output:
 deployment.apps/myngnix created
 4) CHECK POD
 Command:
 kubectl get pods
 Expected Output:- 1 pod Running, READY 1/1
5) EXPOSE DEPLOYMENT AS NODEPORT
 Command:
 kubectl expose deployment myngnix --type=NodePort --port=80 --target-port=80 --name=myngnix
 Expected Output:
 service/myngnix exposed
 6) CHECK SERVICE + NODEPORT
 Command:
 kubectl get service myngnix
 Expected Output:- TYPE = NodePort- PORT(S) = 80:3xxxx/TCP
 7) PORT-FORWARD (WINDOWS FRIENDLY)
 Command:
 kubectl port-forward service/myngnix 30080:80
 Expected Output:
 Forwarding from 127.0.0.1:30080 → 80
 8) OPEN IN BROWSER
 URL:
 http://localhost:30080
 Expected Output:
 ”Welcome to nginx!” webpage
 9) OPEN KUBERNETES DASHBOARD
 Command:
 minikube dashboard
Expected Output:- See pods, deployments, services visually
 10) SCALE DEPLOYMENT (OPTIONAL)
 Command:
 kubectl scale deployment myngnix --replicas=4
 Expected Output:
 4 pods Running (kubectl get pods)
 11) DELETE DEPLOYMENT & SERVICE
 Commands:
 kubectl delete service myngnix
 kubectl delete deployment myngnix
 Expected Output:
 service deleted
 deployment deleted
 12) STOP MINIKUBE
 Command:
 minikube stop
 Expected Output:
 1 node stopped
 IMPORTANT: WHAT TO SHOW EXAMINER
 1) kubectl get pods → Running nginx pod
 2) kubectl get service myngnix → NodePort assigned
 3) Browser showing nginx webpage
